        <q>(7) The Pensions Ombudsman must pay to the Minister for the Civil Service, at such times as he may direct, such sums as he may determine in respect of the increase attributable to subsection (6) in the sums payable out of money provided by Parliament under that Act.</q>
      </p>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_88gc' title='Col. 88GC &mdash; HL Deb 13 October 2004 vol 665 c88GC' name='column_88gc' href='#column_88gc' rel='bookmark'>88GC</a>
